ReferenceDocuments.name: Which of the following racial
ReferenceDocuments.description: Which of the following racial designations best describes you? (More than one choice is acceptable.)

ReferenceDocuments.name: Case Report Form Completion Instructions
ReferenceDocuments.description: Study participants should self-report race, with race being asked about after ethnicity. (The FDA guidance suggests that individuals be permitted to designate a multiracial identity. Check all that apply at the time of collection).

ReferenceDocuments.name: CDISC SDTM Collected Race Terminology
ReferenceDocuments.description: Terminology associated with the race collected codelist of the Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC) Study Data Tabulation Model (SDTM).

ReferenceDocuments.name: SUPPDM.QVAL
ReferenceDocuments.description: This does not map directly to an SDTMIG variable. This information could be submitted in a SUPPDM dataset as the value of SUPPDM.QVAL when SUPPDM.QNAM = "CRACE" and SUPPDM.QLABEL="Collected Race". See the SDTMIG Section for the DM Domain.

ReferenceDocuments.name: CDASH Implementation Notes
ReferenceDocuments.description: Use CRACE when more detailed race categorizations are desired (e.g. more than the five minimum designations for race used by the FDA). The use of race and vocabulary tables located within Health Level Seven's Reference Information Model Structural Vocabulary Tables is recommended, as they are designed to collapse up to the SDTM variable RACE with CT (e.g., American Indian or Alaska Native Asian; Black or African American*; Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander; White ). *For studies where data are collected outside the US, the recommended categories are the same except for Black instead of Black or African American. If multiple races are collected, an alternate sponsor-defined variable structure would be required. Sponsors may record multiple self-reported races for a subject by appending a suffix to denote multiple collected races (e.g. CRACE1, CRACE2) and populate CRACE with the value MULTIPLE. If sponsors, choice to map the extended Race codelist values to the RACE CT (e.g. Japanese to Asian )- then this mapped variable would be reported using the SDTMIG variable RACE. Sponsors should refer to the "Collection of Race and Ethnicity Data in Clinical Trials" (FDA, September 2016).
